          <li><a href="/blog/psychology-of-goals">The Psychology of Goal Setting</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="external-resources">
        <h2>Further Reading</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0065260102800024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Locke & Latham — A Theory of Goal Setting (2002)</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/0956797611404904" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Oettingen — Mental Contrasting and Goal Commitment</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://psycnet.apa.org/record/1977-25094-001" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bandura — Self-Efficacy Research</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="book-recommendations">
        <h2>Recommended Books</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Think and Grow Rich</strong> — Napoleon Hill (the original, 1937 edition)</li>
          <li><strong>Grit</strong> — Angela Duckworth</li>
          <li><strong>Mindset</strong> — Carol Dweck</li>
          <li><strong>The Achievement Habit</strong> — Bernard Roth</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

